SIMPLE: electrograph
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electrograph
<hw>E*lec"tro*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Electro-</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
mark, record, or tracing, made by the action of electricity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An apparatus, controlled by electric devices, used
to trace designs for etching.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An instrument for the reproduction at a distance of
pictures, maps, etc., by means of electricity.</def>
<mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An image made by the R⟦oum⟧ntgen rays; a
sciagraph.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A cinematograph using the arc light.</def>
<mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electrographic</ent>⟦br⟧
